Enel Green, Finmeccanica, Fondiaria May Be Active: Italian Equity Preview

-- B y   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i   a n d   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i
-- 
2011-03-10T07:40:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/enel-green-finmeccanica-fondiaria-may-be-active-italian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index (FTSEMIB)  rose 87.79, or 0.4
percent, to 22,441.24 in Milan.    Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena SpA (BMPS)  : BofA Merrill
Lynch Global Research removed the lender from its “least
preferred” stocks among European banks. The shares rose 0.7
percent to 94.55 euro cents.    Davide Campari-Milano SpA (CPR)  : Goldman Sachs Group
Inc. trimmed its price estimate on the distiller to 5.4 euros
from 5.5 euros. The shares lost 0.8 percent to 4.67 euros.    Edison SpA (EDN)  : Italy’s Finance Minister Giulio
Tremonti asked A2A SpA and its Italian partners not to cede
control of Edison to Electricite da France SA, La Repubblica
reported, without saying where it got the information.  A2A’s boards will meet today to evaluate the situation, the
Italian newspaper said. The shares rose 1.6 percent to 90.7 euro
cents.    Enel Green Power SpA (EGPW)  : The renewable energy unit
of Italy’s biggest utility said profit increased 8.1 percent in
2010 helped by lower taxes and the acquisition of assets in  Spain . The shares gained 3 percent to 1.80 euros.        Finmeccanica SpA (FNC)  : The Italian defense company
agreed to sell a stake in its power-plant construction unit to
U.S. private equity firm First Reserve Corp. after postponing an
initial public offering in 2008. Finmeccanica expects a one-time
net gain of 450 million euros from the sale. The shares rose 3.8
percent to 9.27 euros.    Gruppo Editoriale L’Espresso SpA (ES)  : Citigroup Inc.
lifted its price estimate on the publisher to 1.9 euros from
1.75 euros. The shares added 1.5 percent to 1.97 euros.    Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP)  : BofA Merrill Lynch Global
Research added the lender to its “most preferred” stocks among
European banks. The shares gained 0.3 percent to 2.4 euros.    Mediobanca SpA (MB)  : Morgan Stanley set Mediobanca as
its most preferred name among Italian banks, followed by Intesa
and UniCredit SpA. The brokerage said in a note that all Italian
banks under its coverage should adopt a scrip dividend policy.
Mediobanca shares gained 0.1 percent to 7.62 euros.    Premafin Finanziaria SpA (PF)  : Groupama SA said it’s
studying a new agreement with Italy’s Ligresti family, which
controls Premafin, to comply with requests by Italian stock-
market regulator Consob.  Consob previously said that Groupama would need to make a
full bid on Premafin and its insurer  Fondiaria-Sai SpA (FSA)  
to purchase a stake in the holding controlled by the Ligrestis.
Premafin climbed 4 percent to 77.4 cents. Fondiaria jumped 6.5
percent to 7.57 euros.    Telecom Italia SpA (TIT)  : Italy’s biggest phone company
boosted its stake in Telecom Argentina to 21.1 percent from 18.3
percent after buying an additional 10 percent of Sofora
Telecomunicaciones SA for $145 million. The shares rose 0.2
percent to 1.14 euros.    Tenaris SA (TEN)  : JPMorgan Chase & Co. cut its
recommendation on the world’s largest maker of seamless pipes to
“neutral” from “overweight.” The shares lost 1.4 percent to
16.76 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
